Keldling Bryg
This is a test brew made from 100% Munich malt, East Kent Golding
hops and M44 US West Coast yeast. The Munich malt was mashed at
64°C. It reminds some of nutts, bread or toffee and gives the beer
a bright color (10-15 EBC). East Kent Golding is a classic ale hops with
little bitterness (5% Alpha acids) and some sweet/fresh scents. The yeast
is supposed to add very little flavor. It contained approx.
6,4% alchohol when bottled on the 22nd of July 2016.
"You know, I've never really liked paying bills. I don't suddenly think I'm gonna do that,
either." - "Well, I wouldn't exactly say I've been missing it, Bob." - "I sit in a cubicle
and I update bank software for the 2000 switch" - "I guess that's why I'm working at
Initech." - Peter Gibbons in "Office Space" by Mike Judge.
